						<div class="postbody"><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">It was a Namco 109 mapper, the one used in D*ROM. Tengen used it and called it MIMIC-1.</div>
<br />Yeah and that early verion of MMC3 has only the default CHR ROM and PRG ROM bankswitching. It lacks the alternate switching shemes, IRQ counter and mirroring control.
<br />
<br />MMC3's counter uses A12 which sucks because it forces you to use sprites on the right pattern table and BG on the left, and Konami VRC mappers uses M2 which sucks because it was designed for NTSC only. A good counter would use A13 (like the MMC5 I think).</div>

					
